\c 10
\p
\v 1 King Ahasuerus enacted a payment of tax on the people who were in all the districts of his kingdom from the mainland area, coastal area to the island area.
\v 2 And all the success that had been acheived by King Ahasueros because of his greatness and power were recorded in the history books of the Kings of Media and Persia. Various things that were done by Mordecai, the man who was given authority by the king, was also were written in that book.
\v 3 Mordecai, the Jew who became second under King Ahasuerus was considered as a great person by all the Jews. They truly respected him, because the welfare and peace he had faught for for the entire nation.